Description: 
What does the fiercest financial squeeze in generations 
mean for our personal budgets? And what can we do to 
protect our family finances? In the second of this three-
part series, Sophie Raworth and Justin Rowlatt tackle 
spending and borrowing in these tough economic times. 
From around the country, the Money Watch team report 
on prospects for mortgages, the outlook for prices of 
essentials, hidden catches in credit cards, coping with 
debt and how far you can get by with no money at all.
